content.detailedDescription:
My husband, daughter, and i were in our pool around 10pm and we saw a red light approaching from the south. it was low and we initially thought it was a helicopter- which we see often in our area. however, it was silent; and did not blink. 

it was about 50-55 degrees above the horizon. it appeared to be flying as low as many of the smaller planes and helicopters from the winder and gwinnett airports fly. it changed its course and travelled to the east, toward the moon. we followed it behind the tree line, but it simply disappeared.

naturally, we kept our eyes on the sky. we were excited to see something that we could not identify. just under two minutes later, following the exact same path, was another (or the same) red light. it was silent, in the same position in the sky, and did not blink. it headed east and disappeared right in between us and the moon, as the moon���s light is much brighter. 

other small planes were seen in the sky before and after the sightings; all of which had blinking lights and made sound. i am a scientist, and having eliminated other natural or known manmade flying objects, have decided that this is beyond my scope and would like to see what a more experienced sky-watcher may have to say about this event.
content.summary: Fireball that changed direction and made no sound vanished behind treeline. two minutes later, another one followed the same path.

content.detailedDescription: My daughter took two of these pics from the ocean beach & the other she found on facebook which was posted the same day. she stated this object circled the sun clockwise in less than 5 min.
content.summary: Light w/aura which appeared to orbit the sun

content.detailedDescription: Hi! i live about 7 miles southwest of lax. usually planes do not fly over me. they usually fly around south of me in palos verdes because of noise ordinances here in torrance. normally, we have, in the southbay. a heavy marine layer from the ocean so seeing stars is a real treat when we can. last night i was cleaning my house. it was about 9pm at night. i wasn't tired. and, i went out on the balcony to shake out some rugs in my house. i stopped to notice the marine layer gone and how beautiful the stars were that evening. i looked up towards venus. it's like the largest star. there was about 4 stars that i could make out that night. i had my direction directly above and low and behold there was something moving. it had no lights that were very bright. and it appeared totally black. against the black sky, one would have missed it if they were not looking directly at it. it moved at a normal airplane pace but there was no noise. my line of site followed it. if i looked away, i probably might have lost it. it was heading northwest towards lax in a straight line. planes do not head in that direction usually.  when they land at lax they do so from the east to west on a clear night.  as i tried to make out this opaque plane, i could tell there were 6 dim lights on the bottom of it. these lights followed a triangular pattern on the bottom of the object. my gaze followed it for about 3 to 5 minutes until i could not see it anymore. my first thought was it was heading towards vandenburg air force base. we frequently get a lot of rockets and entrails around that direction. my second thought was that it was some kind of military drone. but, why the triangular shape? and silent, totally silent. or, maybe it was that stealth bomber.  i'm not sure if the stealth bomber is totally silent when it flies.  and does the stealth bomber have about 6 lights on the bottom?  it appeared the same description as the phoenix lights triangle object but not that large.  it's hard to distinguish how big it was or how far away because there was no noise coming from it and that would have given me a frame of reference in deciding how big it was or how far away it was. i thought it was very interesting and left me scratching my head.
content.summary: Silent dim black triangular object seen over los angeles

content.detailedDescription: At 10.00 pm i went outside and immediatly noticed  about six slow moving orange ,silent orbs/fireballs moving in a line from west to east ,horizion to horizion,i went inside to get a camera and had my wife ,niece ,and grandad come out side ,and for the next 20 minutes we saw at least 15-20 more of them  following the same path spread unevenly an some were a degree or two to one side,as we were watching my daughter and sister returned from shopping and said they had also witnessed the event  by vehicle . everyone agreed it was unlike anything they had ever seen before. i did manage to get one decent still of one fireball on my wifes phone  and will upload later today
content.summary: I saw 25-30  orange fireballs movbing slowly in a procession from west to east.

content.detailedDescription: I was at a bar getting a drink and at about 9pm i walked outside with my girlfriend to have a cigarette and i noticed it right away. i pointed to the sky for her to look at it and it was distinct right away. it was flying at incredibly high speed burning red ball looking object. as it was flying our way at about a helicopter height more people joined us to observe it. as it was flying over us it just disappeared in the thin air and we all freaked out. after that the incident just felt so surreal. i was trying to think back of the object but i felt like it was in my dream. and no i wasn't drunk :))
content.summary: Burning object flying much faster than the airplane was moving across the sky and in a split second it disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: theres not a hole lot i can say about this.I found it in a creek.If this is not a real fossilized alien skull then mother nature made one hell of a cool looking rock.I'll just let the picture do the talkin.I have this in my home and want to have it checked for dna.I've had it a couple of years and would love to find out once and for all if its a real alien skull or just a cool looking rock.My opinion is that it looks to real not to be.I know this sight is for ufo sightings but i thought you might want to check this out.I dont know where else to turn to for asking for help with this.You can have all the samples you need.I'm not opposed to you drlling in to it.
content.summary: Fossilised alien skull

content.detailedDescription: The family was outside when we noticed a bright orange light heading west in the sky. we watched it move slowly across the sky, stop, then change direction and head south. it moved extremely slow, like nothing we had ever seen in the sky before. the object sat in the sky for about 10 minutes, changing color from orange, to red, to white. after not moving for a period of time, it disappeared in the blink of an eye.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Orange object heading west, changed direction south, hovered 10 minutes

content.detailedDescription: Me and my wife went out for a smoke and at first we thought it was a meteor passing by earth, but then it changed directions and disappeared, before my wife could run inside and get the camera, it was to fast for a plan and it didn't move like a shooting star.
content.summary: Fast moving object that changed direction then disappeared and was lit up like a ball of fire.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were sitting in our driveway looking at the super moon.  then we looked straight up above us.  at first i thought i was looking at a constellation.  the strange formation of about 16 lights moved extremely fast and never changed its formation.  there was no sound. my husband had run into the house to grab the video camera.  in about the 10 seconds it took for him to come back out they traveled too far out of range for him to capture it.  they were traveling from west to east and i continued staring until i just couldn't see them anymore.
content.summary: Constellation shape of about 16 star lookinglights flew very fast stayed in formation

content.detailedDescription:
Sitting in the backyard with my wife when we noticed an object coming from the west, we are on a flight path for planes coming into toronto pearson airport, but the planes never come in from that direction, so we watched this object. it appeared to be about the same speed as a plane at high altitudes. we knew it wasn't a plane as i did not notice any flashing lights on it. wasn't sure what it was, so got my binoculars, but since they were not very good, couldn't properly focus on it. it had an orangish red glow to it and appeared to be about the size of a bright star. it then slowed down and basically came to a stop which really made me wonder. so we watched and then it just started to slowly disappear right in front of our eyes. i now feel very strange, never seen anything like it and went on line last night and this morning to see if anybody else saw it..Couldn't find nothing and no news on the tv or radio about it! do you have any explanation, would be interested in hearing your comments.
thank you

ps..We both saw it, not a figment of my imagination.
content.summary: Orangish ball came from w heading e, slowed down, stopped in mid air and then began to disintergrate

content.detailedDescription:
I was at the beach last night taking photos of the sun setting. at about 30 minutes after the sun had completely set.  i glanced southward and then witnessed what looked like a blob or smear of several lights over the gulf of mexico. these lights were the same color as a candle flame, perhaps just slightly more red. it looked as if the air itself was ionizing, or there was fire in the air where i was looking. i think the lights were flickering as a fire would from far away, hard to tell for sure. lights together were about the size of a penny in hand outstretched. shape of the lights together was like a backwards l with an apostrophe. it lasted about eight seconds then faded to nothing. 

i did have my camera with me, and no, unfortunately i didn't get a photo. to be honest, by the time i realized i was seeing something out of the ordinary, it was gone, and my camera was on a tripod aimed in the opposite direction.
content.summary: Witnessed a group of lights over the gulf of mexico, looked like fire or air ionizing..

content.detailedDescription: Looked out window towards bright full moon...Noticed 'star'...Pulsating w/red, then white, orange-ish lights on it...Remained somewhat in the same spot.  pulsated/radiated colorful....Got teenage son to check it out, we looked w/binoculars & noticed the same...Must've been in the sky for about 15 minutes....1st time noticing something that i thought was a star, but convinced it was definitely not an airplane or a star...Pretty unsure at this point.
content.summary: Saw beautiful, bright, colorful, pulsating oblong-shaped 'star' hovering in the sky, towards the south.

content.detailedDescription: I saw this blinking light , i thought maybe it was a star but it seemed to be too low to be a star , so i waited to see if it was a plane waiting in a path to land . but after 10 minutes it didn't move . it seems to be pulsating different colors of light . it definitely is under the plane patterns .
content.summary: Blinking star like

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog then just looked up to see how huge the moon was and a  bright orange light to the left of the moon caught my eye, it was roughly 3 to 4 times larger then a star moving across the sky at a fast speed then shifted to the north, flickered acouple times, then dissapeard. i asked my friend if he could hear a helicopter in that direction and he didnt hear anything.
content.summary: Bright huge orange light moving across the sky, changed direction flickered then dissapeard.

content.detailedDescription: Sitting on back patio i observed 4 live rise above the horizon to a elevation that appeared to be about the same. when they neared the same point the light all vanished. full moon out with little to  no clouds...Shortly (2-min) following seeing the initial 4 there where 2 additional light moving in the same direction and vanishing at the same elevation. this occurred over the gulf off or near st pete bch / maderia bch.
content.summary: At 1st there where four light asending all towards same elevation, leading up to six

content.detailedDescription:
Three small white 'orbs' flew over the home, no sound, about , this is a guess, 5,000 to 8,000 feet, i'n a triangular formation at very high speed with no sound. the objects changed direction and as they did so the right object changed direction just hesitant of the other two then went back into formation.  the objects continued on i'n a north easterly direction and went out of site i'n approximately 30 to 45 seconds. 

inwas i'n my back yard wanting to view the full moon as it's the largest of the year.

i was viewing the moon and had just watched several jet liners traverse the area. on seemed to traverse from west to east uncommonly fast about a half hour previous.

i was scanning the sky when suddenly this 'formation' came into view? it was very unusuall , moving very fast and what struck me was it was totally without any noise.

i was shaken by this... the objects moved off to the north east and went out of visual sight i'n about 30 to 45 seconds. very unusual .
content.summary: Three small white objects flying triangular from north to north east right object veered to right as course changed no sound  very high speed

content.detailedDescription: Sitting on my back porch enjoying the evening.  just a large black thing appeared in the direction i was looking (westerly). possibly a black, large balloon?  then a blimp that became kind of "wavy;?"  when i got my binoculars, i couldn't locate it;  then found it very high up in the sky;  moving in a straight direction, while at times rotating while appearing to stop,  with "things" sticking out of object, looking somewhat like  a bug with legs, then again without anything sticking out. by then it had moved in a direction (se) disappearing behind the leaves of my large trees.  i called my friend to search her skies and they saw nothing.  my feelings during this was that it looked quite a bit like the "flying people/witches" i've seen on internet reports of south america. never seen anything like it.  no sound.  very strange.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: And then seen with  binoculars;  rotated without any extensions;  then rotated with "things" sticking out of object.  first looked like a balloon;  then blimp;  then went up out of sight without binoculars;  then with, spotted.  smaller

content.detailedDescription:
Last night behind my apartment building in south austin texas, i was watching the moon, when my girlfriend and i witnessed an unusual light in the sky. the light was about two, (outstretched arm), phone lengths north of the moon.

my girlfriend noticed the object saying it changed altitude very fast. then she brought mt attention to it. it was very noticeable having a starlit or fireball quality about.

at first i thought it was a satellite but soon began doing things that are no indicative of known satellite or aircraft. the movements seem very controlled and sporadic. after each outburst it was joined by a second "light object". then the second "light object" would move away and the movements began again. back and forth, then s curves and circles, in diferrent combinations all very precise.

i felt as if i was watching a hi-tech flight exercise. the second "light object" playing the instructor and the first "light object" would carry out the exercise.

all this lasted for 20 minutes... perhaps a lot longer as it was very cloudy and after this 20 minutes the clouds became so thick we could no longer see anything but cloud.

i filmed about 5 minutes or so on my phone but the "light objects" were to high in the atmosphere to make a visable appearence.
content.summary: Saw two lights in upper atmosphere moving beyond normal flight...

content.detailedDescription: I walked out side to talk to my mom and i happened to look up. i saw a bright light, as bright as venus moving in the sky. i know it was not venus though because venus had set like 7 hours earlier. it was very bright but seemed to have a haze to it. as soon as i saw it i called my mom over and she witnessed this too. the light was moving south west. it then dimmed and changed direction to the east. it traveled some distance then stopped. when it stopped it looked exactly like a faint star. it did not pulsate or anything. right at this moment a shooting star shot through the area and i lost track of the first ufo. a few seconds later another ufo appeared in the same area. i don't think it was the first one because it was 8 inches away at arms distance. anyways, it was yellowish and was traveling towards the south west then slowly turned till it was going south east where it disappeared. there was no sound at all to indicate it was helicopters or jets. the funny part about all this is i had just watched the movie altered which is a really scary alien movie but when i saw these i wasn't afraid at all. all i felt was excitement and wonder.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two bright ufos and a shooting star.

content.detailedDescription: At home in the driveway looking at the moon. saw a bright object in the western sky at about 70 to 90 degrees. we thought it was the space station or a satellite. a second bright object came up behind the first and went above and then below the first object. the second object was going at least 5 to 10 times faster than the first. very fast and bright.No flames or light coming from rear of objects. we felt very strange and the hair was standing up on our arms and back of neck.The object went over horizon and out of sight.
content.summary: One object went over another, two bright objects, very high, very strange.

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend and i where at home watching t.V. and received a phone call at 10:02pm last night from a friend who frantically told us to go outside and look into the sky. this excited us after seeing numerous orbs in the sky last summer above our house we immediately ran outside. we attempted several different recording methods but we couldn't get good video. our 12 year old daughter was also with us and witnessed her first sighting. we witnessed 15+ orbs moving upward into the cloud line and from our perspective we could see just above the clouds where the orbs should have become visible again. but did not! they vanished!
we witnessed several of the orbs glowing in and out almost to the point of fading out and then getting brighter as they moved oddly up into the sky! this lasted roughly 20 minutes from begging to end. we did not see it start so its unclear on how long this event lasted. in total there were 3 friends in the car who called us to tell us about the orbs and there was myself my girlfriend and our 12 year old daughter so at least 5 other people besides myself that i know of saw the event!I personally felt very overwhelmed at first but then felt hypnotized by its wonder and felt calm and peace. very weird emotion.
content.summary: Bright colored orbs ascending into the clouds and disappearing above the cloud line!

content.detailedDescription: Seven friends and i where having a conversation out side when my buddy pointed up and calmly asked "what is that". we all turn around and witness two fireball like spheres glided in-sync across the sky heading westward. did not make any sounds or any change in elevation before disappearing over the tree line.  we all stayed calm and unaffected during and after the sighting. i'm a sceptic of this type of thing so i would really like to know what it was and if anyone else can account for this. i noticed a post on this site of almost the exact same event which happened a year ago to the day. make me wonder if it an annual flight test of some kind.
content.summary: Two fireball like spheres glided in-sync across the sky heading westward. did not make any sounds or any change in elevation before disappearing over the tree line.

content.detailedDescription: I went outside my apartment to smoke a cigarette. i looked up in the sky to look at the stars. i knew at first it was not a jet or plane because they were moving so fast and were so bright. they were traveling from south to north in an almost perfect v formation. i think they were all individual craft in formation because the v wasn't perfectly aligned.  chills went down my spine as i witnessed it .
content.summary: 13 lights flying in a v formation going across the whole sky in four or five seconds like a shooting star

content.detailedDescription:
I just pulled into my driveway on my way home from work; when out of the corner of my eye i notice strange lights.  i'm very into astrology and look up at the sky every night.  what i saw surprise me.  it was 4 reddish / orange star like circles in the sky.  they were pointed towards buffalo ( west )  roughly 500ft in the sky and were about the size a normal star. they were in a diagnoal line that was shape the same as the big dippers handle.

. 
  

    . 
  

         . 
  

               .    this would be an example of how it appeared.

i study the moving objects for about a minute.  they all move from right to left and then traveled upward at about the same speed.  it was noticeably slow.  look around 10-30mph if i had to make a guess.  about a minute later they disappeared " or fizzed " out.

i would say the lights were directly over the town of lancaster/depew.  if i had to make a guess, they were flairs; but being over a town made it very odd.  the reason flairs didn't make too much sense is because of the flight path.  they were falling but moving right to left and then up.  making it very strange.  but they did have a "fiery"  glow to them like mars does.

i tried taking a picture / recording a video on my phone but my camera quality is too weak to pick it up.   

very strange.
content.summary: Star like / flair / or weather ballon

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home south on i-435 in kansas when i saw a bright star, that did not look familiar in the sky, near the big dipper. i've been watching the night sky a lot recently for multiple reasons, the ancient alien theory intrigues me and i think i have figured out what it all means and i do believe that they will return in 2012. so ive been looking up since the new year. i observed the light as bright but distant, further south. and as i drove near home the light, though stationary, became negligibly bigger. i arrived home and went to my room and looked outside. it was still there i got on google and searched images of the big dipper to see if i could explain what id seen.. but i couldn't. so i turned back out the window and then the star was gone.
content.summary: Bright star hovering near big dipper.

content.detailedDescription:
Sitting with some friends at coffee when one of them facing me said "hey, what's that?" and pointed to something behind me. i turned around to see what was clearly a helicopter or airplane flying but surrounding it a little further in the distance were 4 "orbs", glowing orange/red. looked like they could have possibly been in a v formation, but not a part of one unit, and the angle at which we were looking at them made it also difficult to tell if there was a true formation in the flying pattern. the orbs did not hover but rather continued to move in a straight line and then one at a time each orb slowly dimmed out until none of them could be seen anymore. this happened in about a minute time span, maybe slightly more or less. nothing more was seen and the helicopter/airplane just continued on it's way. 

i was present during the first phoenix lights in az and saw them first hand. although these did not hover or seem to be in a clear flying formation, the color and shape seemed very similar to the first sighting in 1997. 

i am not a huge ufo person and i am not a person who would typically seek out this kind of site, however this is not the first time i have seen this in the last couple years and it frequently seems to be unreported, as if no one else saw it. so, i thought i would throw this out there and see if anyone else saw what i saw. i was at mcclintock and southern when it happened in tempe.
content.summary: 4 bright red/orange orbs, flew straight & disappeared
